tasks.description:
Add double-click lightbox for media clips in preview overlay.

Files: `src/tools/video-editor/components/PreviewPanel/OverlayEditor.tsx`, `src/tools/video-editor/components/PreviewPanel/PreviewPanel.tsx`, `src/tools/video-editor/components/PropertiesPanel/AssetPanel.tsx` (extract helper)

Data dependency chain: OverlayEditor has `registry` (maps asset keys → `ResolvedAssetRegistryEntry` with `generationId`) → need `loadGenerationForLightbox` query → need `GenerationRow` for `MediaLightbox`.

1. Extract `loadGenerationForLightbox` from AssetPanel.tsx:49-97 into a shared file (e.g., `src/tools/video-editor/lib/generation-utils.ts`). Import from both AssetPanel and PreviewPanel.
2. In OverlayEditor.tsx:390, extend double-click handler:
   ```tsx
   onDoubleClick={() => {
     if (clipMeta?.clipType === 'text') {
       beginTextEdit(overlay.actionId);
     } else if (clipMeta?.asset) {
       onDoubleClickAsset?.(clipMeta.asset);
     }
   }}
   ```
3. Add `onDoubleClickAsset?: (assetKey: string) => void` to OverlayEditorProps.
4. In PreviewPanel.tsx, add `useState<string | null>` for `lightboxAssetKey`. Wire callback to OverlayEditor.
5. Render `MediaLightbox` in PreviewPanel using `loadGenerationForLightbox` for the selected asset's `generationId` (from `registry[assetKey]?.generationId`).
6. Graceful fallback: if no `generationId`, double-click does nothing (no error).
